##Vernal Equinox, I greedily with the sound of the window perception of spring

WECHAT betteryourlife2013

The introduction to better your life focuses on the better you and the better world that comes with it.

It's the Spring Equinox, and we haven't had a chance to realize that the spring of 2020 is coming to an end.

This spring is destined to be remembered. It will come back to us in the spring, some time later, when we suddenly relax.

That spring, we didn't leave the house. Instead, after being closed for nearly two months, we watched a live cherry blossom broadcast on the Internet with one million people.

In the spring of that year, we met a lot of people, the whistle blower who disappeared, the medical workers who rushed to the front, the Wuhan sisters-in-law who were scolded passionately, and countless volunteers.

The spring of this year is white, a piece of paper notice, a piece of protective clothing and some too late to say goodbye to the Pale farewell.

The spring of the year is covered with many smells, the smell of grass, the smell of non-woven fabric masks, the smell of disinfectant, the smell of alcohol volatilization.

This spring we hear many sounds, ordinary or special, meaningful or meaningless.

They make up the spring of 2020 in Wuhan.

Birds Chirping ]
@ twenty-four

Hazy, by the community disinfection trailer after the harsh sound wake up, generally need to sleep a return to sleep to fully awake. Will Not consciously ask themselves "today number, today, day of the week, " thinking for a moment and then feel meaningless. When I went to the bathroom, my upstairs neighbor's voice came down the drain through the window, and through several walls, I could clearly hear my grandmother and granddaughter laughing about sweet corn and sticky corn.

I couldn't help but stop what I was doing and put my ear closer to the window, acting perverted just to hear more conversation, which made me feel safe. But the conversation stopped, leaving only the chirping of the birds in the other direction.

The sound of birds, which is usually pleasing to the ear, is nothing compared to the noise which is usually regarded as noise, for only the human voice can make everything seem normal.

An empty neighborhood garden

On the balcony, the bright sunlight slanted on the dirty clothes basket, the static good picture let me forget the body's pajamas have worn nearly 30 days. Spring in Wuhan is short, this year's spring clothing is beyond hope.

Quietly, downstairs the pink flowers opened, the wind has faded cold, how I wish it was just an ordinary Saturday morning.

[ dog barks ]
@ I'm sorry

This spring, I often wake up in the middle of the day in the middle of a loud, shouting family conversation downstairs. This in ordinary times seems close to the noise of the voice, has turned out to be rare in the epidemic can be exposed to the "popularity. ".

The one downstairs has a big sky terrace with flowers, vegetables, cats and dogs. It had been so long since I'd moved here that I'd learned that all the dog barks I hear every day come from three small, black, unknown breeds.

These days, I sit on the balcony and watch their dogs fight and yell, run and lie there quietly. I even experienced the thrill of stealing other people's happiness and getting a weird sense of satisfaction.

Sometimes I feel strangely envious of them —— As if this spring, they had an open space to frolic in and feel the breeze on their faces, without having to peer through the window at the new flowers, we don't have to worry about a pandemic that we don't know when will be over.

When will spring come for us?

[ mowing grass ]
@ Duck

On a quiet afternoon, there was a buzzing noise outside the house. Peering out, it turned out to be a sanitation worker mowing the lawn.

She wore thick protective clothing, fully armed walking in a blossoming winter jasmine. After the rain unique earthy fragrance also at this time drilling into my nose, is really a memorable taste. It had been nearly two months since the siege, and the image of the outside world had begun to blur.

The grass is tall, the wind is warm, the Cherry blossoms are in bloom, and spring is here, and the countdown to the end of the epidemic has begun. I'm sure you'll be rolling around in the grass in no time.

Sunset outside a window in Wuhan on March 18

["Go Wuhan" ]
@Ailsa

January 27,20:00, many Wuhan residents in the community spontaneously open windows collectively high-pitched songs "March of the Volunteers" and "I and my Motherland" , the community radio also followed the "accompaniment. From then on, it became more and more neat and sonorous, as if everyone would express and release the panic, bewilderment, depression and pain caused by the sudden epidemic in the shouting and singing.

"Wuhan refuels" these four words not only to Wuhan's blessing and the prayer, also is us to give own encouragement. Looking forward to the day of recovery in Wuhan, looking forward to the spring in full bloom.

[ friends singing ]
This symbol points to the north

This spring, I was alone in Wuhan. The Room is always quiet, even when playing video games, there is only the sound of typing.

Isolation and silence give people an excuse to relax. At least in the game, I'm not alone. That time, I saw my best friend in high school online, though I hadn't talked to her for a long time, I don't know if the relationship is still the same, but I still worked up the courage to ask her to play with me.

Since then, I have found a somewhat "noisy" way of coping, is to play games with her on time every day. Every day at three o'clock in the afternoon, my laughter would drown out everything in the room.

A small amusement park abandoned during the outbreak

We Watch legend of Zhen Huan together when we're not playing the game, and we talk about the joke in legend of Zhen Huan together when we're playing the game. I laughed so hard when I heard her sing this song several times, and many times I didn't help her properly, and all of a sudden she's like, "you work for me? "

It was days like this that made me feel like I was back in high school. It's like, innocent teenagers live in our hearts all the time, and as long as we press the Stop Button, teenagers don't grow up, they stay young, and they stay fun.

Community Radio ]
@ I'm sorry

"The owners of the new type of pneumonia prevention and control is now extraordinary period, please owners as little as possible to go out, more ventilation, frequent hand washing, wearing a mask... "

The sound of the radio in the community will be sounded every day at 4 p.m. Sharp. The security guard carried a loudspeaker and walked around the small central garden to complete today's notice.

The security guard shaving his head

By this time, the sound of the ball on the basketball court was clear, the laughter of the children in the playground and the babble of the teeter-totter spring. Spring is supposed to be a season of indulgence and pleasure, but this year, silence masks the Din and emptiness replaces the crowd.

It's almost April, and spring is on its way.

[ sterilizing vehicle BGM ]
@ Gao Yuxin

From the moment I was shut in, I became interested in everything outside my window (the last time I felt this way was when I was doing my homework in my senior year) , and the car that was waiting for me to drive into the neighborhood at 3 p.m. was the happiest thing I had ever done.

When the AUTOCLAVE'S BGM rang, I ran out onto the balcony like an enlightened believer and watched in silence.

I saw an uncle on the other side of the building open the window as aggressively as I did, and even waved at me. In the rare music of this spring, we are all greedily absorbing the subtle pleasures that can be felt.

[ CART WHEELS whirring ]
@Ailsa

Fengcheng, Fengqu, self-procurement has become a small group purchase, every household every time the purchase of large quantities of living materials, as if to let the home as a "small wholesale market" , a large number of hoarding living materials, in order to obtain peace of mind.

People around us are consciously cutting back on travel and mobility. On weekdays, when staying at home, I can occasionally hear other owners in the community pushing a trolley out the door, and the sound of the roller and the ground rubbing from far and near, or from near and far, to really feel that there are still a lot of people living in this empty city.

Bell tolling ]
@ Carrefour pirates

When you wake up at night, it's quiet. Lying in bed, I heard for the first time in the room the sound of three second hands moving.

When I was at school, in order to remind myself that "time is running out" , I set the three clocks in my room forward by 5-10 minutes.

I haven't lived at home for so long since I graduated from college, and I've forgotten how fast I set the clock. And that night, when I heard the ticking of three clocks, I remembered.

After that day, the three hours became more present. I would sit at my desk and watch the second hand go to 12 and the minute hand take another step away from the next number. What used to be seen as a time-waster has become a well-deserved spring break.

After all, this spring has left us with nothing but time.

Get up at 9 am, have breakfast at 9.30 am, clean your room at 10 am, sit at your desk and start working or reading after spending half an hour with your family watching the news. Eat at 2 pm, do the dishes at 3 pm and sit at your desk at 3.30 pm until 7 pm. After dinner with the News Network, work out at 8, shower at 9, go to bed at 9:30, watch a movie at 12, go to bed... so, copy paste like start of the day.

It's been a spring of no-holds-barred dates, but we've still got the habit of flag, only it's been "unsealed. ".

Have you noticed that the things you didn't do last winter, you still won't do this spring. Locked up in our homes, we hear the sound of time passing, but we don't put things on the agenda that we should have done a long time ago.

If you wanted to do it, you would have done it already.
